[Inyo County can be seen on the map at http://geology.com/county-map/california-county-map.gif. - Sr.Tech.Ed.MJ

Primary amebic meningoencephalitis from free living amoeba including _Naegleria fowleri_ and others are ubiquitous, and sporadic cases are seen after contact with fresh water during warm weather. Lately, ProMED-mail has reported a series of cases from Pakistan, which seems to be related to nasal irrigation with contaminated water (see postings listed below). - Mod.EP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3488234,41428.]
